{
    "title": "Go-To-Market: Startup Product Launch",
    "description": "Comprehensive GTM playbook for startup product launches incorporating best-in-class methodologies: Jobs-to-be-Done, April Dunford's positioning framework, crossing the chasm strategy, RICE prioritization, and lean startup validation. Covers market research through launch and scale.",
    "version": 1,
    "channel_name_template": "gtm-<name>",
    "message_on_join_enabled": true,
    "message_on_join": "**Go-To-Market War Room**\n\nThis channel coordinates our product launch. All GTM decisions, research findings, and launch activities are tracked here.\n\n**GTM Team:**\n- Product Lead: @[to be assigned]\n- Marketing Lead: @[to be assigned]\n- Sales Lead: @[to be assigned]\n- Customer Success: @[to be assigned]\n- Founder/CEO: @[to be assigned]\n\n**Methodology:**\nThis playbook incorporates Jobs-to-be-Done, April Dunford's positioning framework, Geoffrey Moore's Crossing the Chasm, and Lean Startup validation principles.\n\n**Key Documents:**\n- Market Research: [Link]\n- Positioning Canvas: [Link]\n- Launch Plan: [Link]",
    "run_summary_template_enabled": true,
    "run_summary_template": "**GTM Overview**\n\n**Product:** \n**Target Launch:** \n**Target Market:** \n**ICP:** \n\n**Positioning Statement:**\nFor [target customer] who [statement of need], [product name] is a [category] that [key benefit]. Unlike [alternatives], we [key differentiator].\n\n**GTM Motion:** (Product-Led / Sales-Led / Hybrid)\n**Pricing Model:** \n**Initial Target:** (Beachhead Market)\n\n**Key Metrics:**\n- CAC Target: $\n- LTV Target: $\n- Conversion Target: %\n\n**Phase:** (Research / Validation / Pre-Launch / Launch / Scale)\n**Status:** (On Track / At Risk / Blocked)",
    "status_update_enabled": true,
    "reminder_timer_default_seconds": 259200,
    "retrospective_enabled": true,
    "retrospective_reminder_interval_seconds": 604800,
    "retrospective_template": "### GTM Launch Retrospective\n\n### Results vs Goals\n| Metric | Target | Actual | % of Goal |\n|--------|--------|--------|----------|\n| Signups/Leads | | | |\n| Conversions | | | |\n| Revenue | | | |\n| CAC | | | |\n| NPS | | | |\n\n### Positioning Effectiveness\n- Did our positioning resonate? Evidence:\n- Message testing results:\n- Competitive differentiation clarity:\n\n### Channel Performance\n| Channel | Spend | Results | CAC | Notes |\n|---------|-------|---------|-----|-------|\n| | | | | |\n\n### Customer Feedback\n- Top positive feedback:\n- Top concerns/objections:\n- Feature requests:\n- Unexpected use cases:\n\n### What Worked\n- Positioning/messaging:\n- Channels:\n- Sales process:\n- Product:\n\n### What Didn't Work\n- Positioning/messaging:\n- Channels:\n- Sales process:\n- Product gaps:\n\n### Key Learnings\n- About our customer:\n- About our market:\n- About our product:\n- About our process:\n\n### Adjustments for Scale Phase\n- Positioning changes:\n- Channel reallocation:\n- Pricing adjustments:\n- Product roadmap impact:\n\n### Action Items\n| Action | Owner | Due Date |\n|--------|-------|----------|",
    "signal_any_keywords_enabled": true,
    "signal_any_keywords": [
        "product launch",
        "go to market",
        "GTM",
        "launch plan",
        "market entry"
    ],
    "metrics": [],
    "checklists": [
        {
            "title": "Phase 1: Market Research & Analysis",
            "items": [
                {"title": "Define research objectives and key questions"},
                {"title": "MARKET SIZE: Calculate TAM (Total Addressable Market)"},
                {"title": "MARKET SIZE: Calculate SAM (Serviceable Addressable Market)"},
                {"title": "MARKET SIZE: Calculate SOM (Serviceable Obtainable Market)"},
                {"title": "RESEARCH: Industry reports gathered (Gartner, Forrester, CB Insights)"},
                {"title": "RESEARCH: Competitor analysis completed (direct & indirect)"},
                {"title": "RESEARCH: Market trends identified"},
                {"title": "RESEARCH: Regulatory/compliance requirements documented"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: What macro trends are driving this market?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: What is the market growth rate?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Where is the market in its lifecycle?"},
                {"title": "COMPETITIVE: Identify top 5-10 competitors"},
                {"title": "COMPETITIVE: Map competitor positioning (2x2 matrix)"},
                {"title": "COMPETITIVE: Document competitor pricing"},
                {"title": "COMPETITIVE: Identify competitor strengths/weaknesses"},
                {"title": "COMPETITIVE: Find gaps in market not being served"},
                {"title": "Document market entry barriers"},
                {"title": "Market research summary created"},
                {"title": "EXIT: Market opportunity validated and sized"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Phase 2: Customer Discovery (Jobs-to-be-Done)",
            "items": [
                {"title": "Identify initial customer hypotheses"},
                {"title": "JTBD: What job is the customer trying to get done?"},
                {"title": "JTBD: What are the functional aspects of the job?"},
                {"title": "JTBD: What are the emotional aspects of the job?"},
                {"title": "JTBD: What are the social aspects of the job?"},
                {"title": "JTBD: When does the job arise? (Trigger events)"},
                {"title": "JTBD: What are customers hiring today to do this job?"},
                {"title": "JTBD: What makes current solutions inadequate?"},
                {"title": "Conduct 20+ customer discovery interviews"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: What problem are you trying to solve?"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: Tell me about the last time you experienced this problem"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: What have you tried? What worked/didn't work?"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: How are you solving this today?"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: What would your ideal solution look like?"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: How much time/money does this problem cost you?"},
                {"title": "INTERVIEW: Would you pay for a solution? How much?"},
                {"title": "Synthesize interview findings"},
                {"title": "Identify patterns in customer responses"},
                {"title": "Validate problem-solution fit"},
                {"title": "Document customer quotes and evidence"},
                {"title": "EXIT: Clear understanding of JTBD and customer pain"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Phase 3: ICP & Segmentation",
            "items": [
                {"title": "Define Ideal Customer Profile (ICP)"},
                {"title": "ICP FIRMOGRAPHICS: Industry/vertical"},
                {"title": "ICP FIRMOGRAPHICS: Company size (employees)"},
                {"title": "ICP FIRMOGRAPHICS: Revenue range"},
                {"title": "ICP FIRMOGRAPHICS: Geography"},
                {"title": "ICP FIRMOGRAPHICS: Tech stack/infrastructure"},
                {"title": "ICP BEHAVIOR: Buying triggers"},
                {"title": "ICP BEHAVIOR: Decision-making process"},
                {"title": "ICP BEHAVIOR: Budget cycle"},
                {"title": "ICP PERSONA: Title/role of buyer"},
                {"title": "ICP PERSONA: Title/role of user"},
                {"title": "ICP PERSONA: Title/role of decision maker"},
                {"title": "ICP PERSONA: Goals and KPIs"},
                {"title": "ICP PERSONA: Daily challenges"},
                {"title": "SEGMENTATION: Identify 3-5 distinct segments"},
                {"title": "SEGMENTATION: Size each segment"},
                {"title": "SEGMENTATION: Assess segment attractiveness"},
                {"title": "BEACHHEAD: Select initial target segment (Crossing the Chasm)"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Why this segment first?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Can we dominate this segment?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Will this segment lead to adjacent segments?"},
                {"title": "Create detailed buyer personas (2-3)"},
                {"title": "Map buying committee for B2B"},
                {"title": "ICP document finalized"},
                {"title": "EXIT: Clear ICP and beachhead market defined"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Phase 4: Positioning (April Dunford Framework)",
            "items": [
                {"title": "COMPETITIVE ALTERNATIVES: What would customers use if we didn't exist?"},
                {"title": "UNIQUE ATTRIBUTES: What features/capabilities do only we have?"},
                {"title": "VALUE: What value do those attributes enable?"},
                {"title": "VALUE: Translate features to customer outcomes"},
                {"title": "WHO CARES: Which customers care most about this value?"},
                {"title": "MARKET CATEGORY: What market do we position in?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Do we create a new category or enter existing?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: If new category, how do we explain it?"},
                {"title": "Develop positioning statement"},
                {"title": "Test positioning with 10+ target customers"},
                {"title": "Refine based on feedback"},
                {"title": "MESSAGING: Craft primary value proposition"},
                {"title": "MESSAGING: Develop 3 supporting proof points"},
                {"title": "MESSAGING: Create elevator pitch (30 seconds)"},
                {"title": "MESSAGING: Create extended pitch (2 minutes)"},
                {"title": "MESSAGING: Develop objection handling"},
                {"title": "Create positioning canvas document"},
                {"title": "DIFFERENTIATION: 'Only we...' statement"},
                {"title": "Messaging tested and validated"},
                {"title": "EXIT: Positioning locked and documented"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Phase 5: Pricing Strategy",
            "items": [
                {"title": "RESEARCH: Document competitor pricing"},
                {"title": "RESEARCH: Customer willingness-to-pay interviews"},
                {"title": "VALUE-BASED: Calculate customer value delivered"},
                {"title": "VALUE-BASED: Identify value metric (what drives pricing)"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: What pricing model? (Subscription/Usage/Seat/Flat)"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: What pricing tiers? (Free/Pro/Enterprise)"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Do we offer freemium? Why/why not?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: Annual vs monthly pricing?"},
                {"title": "QUESTION: What discount structure for annual?"},
                {"title": "Calculate unit economics"},
                {"title": "METRICS: Target CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost)"},
                {"title": "METRICS: Target LTV (Lifetime Value)"},
                {"title": "METRICS: LTV:CAC ratio (target >3:1)"},
                {"title": "METRICS: Payback period target"},
                {"title": "Price sensitivity testing (Van Westendorp or Gabor-Granger)"},
                {"title": "Define pricing page structure"},
                {"title": "Create pricing FAQ"},
                {"title": "Enterprise/custom pricing process defined"},
                {"title": "Discount approval matrix created"},
                {"title": "Pricing strategy documented"},
                {"title": "EXIT: Pricing model finalized and tested"}
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Phase 6: GTM Motion & Channels",
            "items": [
                {"title": "DECISION: GTM motion (Product-Led / Sales-Led / Hybrid)"},
                {"title": "PRODUCT-LED: Self-serve signup flow designed"},
                {"title": "PRODUCT-LED: Free trial or freemium strategy"},
                {"title": "PRODUCT-LED: Activation metrics defined"},
                {"title": "PRODUCT-LED: Upgrade triggers identified"},
                {"title": "SALES-LED: Sales process mapped"},
